ARTICLE IX. HIGHWAY BUSINESS DISTRICT (HB)
152.080 DISTRICT DESCRIPTION
The purpose of this district shall be to provide for the proper grouping and development of roadside
business uses, and for uses not basically related to central or neighborhood business areas.
152.081 PERMITTED USES
(a) Accessory use;
(b) Ambulance service;
(c) Animal medical care (no kennels);
(d) Banks, savings and loans financial activities;
(e) Barber shops, beauty shops, nail salons and spas;
(f) Bed and breakfast, tourist homes, or boarding houses;
(g) Boat and accessory sales and service;
(h) Building supplies;
(i) Bus terminals;
(j) Professional Services;
(k) Churches and related use;
(I) Clubs or lodges (civic or fraternal)
(m) Clinic;
(n) Cultural or community facility;
(o) Dry cleaning and laundry service;
